definition.value: This is an AE which is often implicated in primary ischemic stroke secondary to thrombosis or embolism and may indicate concurrent cardiovascular disease.
This is an AE which refers blockage of a carotid artery  blood vessel.

This is an AE which is a long lasting and continuously evolving disease with multiple clinical manifestations ranging from asymptomatic to stable angina, acute coronary syndrome (ACS), heart failure (HF) and sudden cardiac death (SCD).
This is an AE which is a surgical procedure to restore normal blood flow to an obstructed coronary artery.
This is an AE which is an abnormal dilatation of part of the coronary artery.
This is an AE which occurs when blood flow decreases or stops to the coronary artery of the heart, causing damage to the heart muscle.
This is an AE which involves the reduction of blood flow to the heart muscle due to build-up of plaque (atherosclerosis) in the arteries of the heart.
This is an AE which occurs when an injury to the innermost layer of the  coronary aorta allows blood to flow between the layers of the aortic wall, forcing the layers apart.
This is an AE which is the lodging of an embolus, a blockage-causing piece of material, inside a femoral artery blood vessel.
This is an AE which refers blockage of a femoral artery  blood vessel.
This is an AE which is an inflammatory autoimmune disease of large blood vessels.
This is an AE which refers blockage of a iliac vein  blood vessel.
This is an AE which is an abnormal narrowing of arteries other than those that supply the heart or brain.
This is an AE which refers blockage of a peripheral artery blood vessel.
This is an AE which refers blockage of a peripheral vein blood vessel.
This is an AE which is the inflammation of a vein, usually in the legs.
This is an AE which presents in the umbilical cord.
This is an AE which is a significant form of peripheral artery disease, which may be a marker of diffuse atherosclerosis and increased risk for cardiovascular events.

This is an AE which is a form of large vessel granulomatous vasculitis with massive intimal fibrosis and vascular narrowing, most commonly affecting young or middle-age women of Asian descent, though anyone can be affected.
This is an AE which is an inflammatory autoimmune disease of large blood vessels.
This is an AE which is a rare form of congenital heart disease that presents at birth.
This is an AE which is a congenital defect of the pulmonary veins.
This is an AE which is the catheter site  inflammation of a vein, usually in the legs.
This is an AE which is a frequent finding in patients with cirrhosis and portal hypertension, and may be produced by various mechanisms.
This is an AE which is an abnormal narrowing in a blood vessel or other tubular organ such as inferior vena cava or structure such as foramina and canals.
This is an AE which is the indirectly observed pressure over the venous system via visualization of the internal jugular vein.
This is an AE which is the most common type of congenital vascular malformation.
This is an AE which may be an ocular complication of Buerger's disease.
This is an AE which is the inflammation of a vein and is deep.
This is an AE which is a small local, usually rounded, calcification within a vein.

This is an AE which is part of the complex biological response of portal tract tissues to harmful stimuli, such as pathogens, damaged cells, or irritants, and is a protective response involving immune cells, blood vessels, and molecular mediators.
This is an AE which is a rare finding on radiological exams.
This is an AE which results in venous hypertension with the formation of intra- and extrarenal collaterals and/or the development of gonadal vein reflux.
This is an AE which is the lodging of an renal vein embolus, a blockage-causing piece of material, inside a blood vessel.
This is an AE which has been often reported to be associated with acute decompensated heart failure and, to our knowledge.

This is an AE which is characterized clinically by a local syndrome in an arm, the chest or a leg, by an irregular temperature (toothsaw curve), by blood cultures that are simultaneously or successively positive for one or several pathogenic microorganisms, by repeated, multiple infected embolism and by the possibility of endocarditis as a complication.
This is an AE which is a vein that is close to the surface of the body and is prominent.
This is an AE which is important features of advanced heart failure.
This is an AE which is the build-up of fluid in the visceral  tissue.
This is an AE which is pain that results from the activation of nociceptors of the thoracic, pelvic, or abdominal viscera (organs).
This is an AE which is a prolapse or a sinking of the abdominal viscera (internal organs) below their natural position.
This is an AE which is a group of abnormal heart rhythms (arrhythmias) usually caused by a malfunction of the sinus node, the heart's primary pacemaker.
This is an AE which is an abnormal growth of sinus tissue projecting from a mucous membrane.
This is an AE which is any cardiac rhythm in which depolarisation of the cardiac muscle begins at the sinus node.
This is an AE which is a commonly encountered variation of normal sinus rhythm.
This is an AE which is a form of iron overload disorder resulting in the accumulation of hemosiderin.
This is an AE which indicates accumulation of iron in the body from any cause.

This is an AE which maternal IgG antibodies with specificity for the ABO blood group system pass through the placenta to the fetal circulation where they can cause hemolysis of fetal red blood cells which can lead to fetal anemia and HDN.
This is an AE which is a condition of the mucous membranes characterized by the sudden appearance of one or more blood blisters within the oral cavity.
This is an AE which frequently results in death, prompt treatment may result in full recovery .
